Considerations for Data Stream Field Disablement

There are few restrictions to consider when planning to disable a data stream field.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Edition
Common Considerations

You can't disable these types of data stream fields.

Fields used as part of the Primary Key, Event Date Time, Organization Unit Identifier or Record Modified fields.
System-generated fields such as Data Source, Data Source Object, cdp_sys_SourceVersion, and Internal Organization.
Fields used as source fields in any other formula field.
Fields of a data stream that is deployed from a Package.
Fields of data stream ingesting data from Marketing Cloud Engagement, Engagement data extensions, and Mobile SDK streams.
Considerations for Disabling a Field in CRM
To delete a field from your connected CRM, first disable that field from Data Cloud to avoid ingestion errors in data streams.
After you disable a field, you can delete the field through the connected Salesforce CRM Object Manager admin tool. Then remove the field from the Data Cloud permission set in that connected Salesforce CRM.
